Using Gitkraken:

1) open Gitkraken app

2) test connection to Github:
	- Go to File -> Preferences -> Integrations -> GitHub
	- Should show connected
	- If disconnected:
		- open Firefox (needs to run in background)
		- go back to GitHub
		- Click on 'Connect to github'
		- may ask for username and password: 
			username: BriggsNeuro 
			password: Ferrets2020!@%
	- Exit preferences 		

3) To get new experiment files:
	- Go to PLDAPSBL tab
	- Click 'Pull' (middle of top toolbar)
	- if 'main' is next to the computer symbol and the blue/white symbol, you are up to date
	
4) To upload changes:
	- Go to PLDAPSBL tab
	- on the top of the list should be an item called '//WIP' - click on that if not already selected
	- edited files will show up under 'unstaged files' in the top window on the right
	- click 'stage all changes' to move them one window down (staged files)
	- type a short description into the commit window where is says 'commit summary'
	- hit commit changes button on bottom right
	- click 'push' (top toolbar)
	- again, main, the computer icon and the blue/white icon should appear next to each other

